{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/personal-url-shortener-with-netlify-redirects/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"05eabdd5-cc42-59cf-8207-3d71c949db9c","html":"<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@ozarkdrones?utm_source=unsplash&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Ozark Drones</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/uturn?utm_source=unsplash&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\n<p>I love using URL shorteners to easily share links without hitting character limits, but they loose their meaning. Services like bit.ly will save my links for me so that I can find them, but I would rather them to be easy to remember. <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2ruLwQz\" title=\"https://bit.ly/2ruLwQz\">https://bit.ly/2ruLwQz</a> does not roll of the tongue so well.</p>\n<h1>301 ü§∏‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è</h1>\n<p>I recently discovered a really cool feature of netlify that I have always looked past, <code class=\"language-text\">_redirects</code>. It is so simple cool and powerful, every netlify site should do this!</p>\n<h1>But how ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è</h1>\n<p>simply add a <code class=\"language-text\">_redirects</code> file to the root of your your published site with the following format. The trick I found with my gatsby site was that it needed to be in my static directory <code class=\"language-text\">/static/_redirects</code>, not root. Next you just put space separated links on separate lines. #'s can be used for comments.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"markdown\"><pre class=\"language-markdown\"><code class=\"language-markdown\"><span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> netlify redirects</span>\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> from_url to_url</span>\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> Short-Blog</span>\n\n/blog/scli         /blog/simple-click/\n/blog/cmdt         /blog/cmd-exe-tips/\n.\n.\n.\n\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> splats</span>\n\n/b<span class=\"token italic\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">*</span><span class=\"token content\">             /blog/:splat\n/n</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">*</span></span>             /notes/:splat\n\n\n<span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> External</span>\n\n/twitter        https://twitter.com/_WaylonWalker\n/github         https://github.com/WaylonWalker\n/devto          https://dev.to/waylonwalker/</code></pre></div>\n<h1>üôå Share those short links</h1>\n<p>Now with shorter links we have more space for our content without needing to use a service like bit.ly that makes our links unreadable.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../../static/URL%20shortener.png\" alt=\"url shortener\"></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2020-01-29T06:00:00.000Z","devto_url":null,"devto_id":null,"title":"Personal URL shortener with Netlify Redirects","description":"Personal URL shortener with Netlify Redirects","path":"personal-url-shortener","twitter_cover":{"id":"d4f05d44-e9f3-57e7-bcbb-2c6457ed3211","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/URL shortener.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"6eeb0357-4577-5323-b8f3-12367bbdcba6","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":800,"height":418,"src":"/static/2e0c5b239e172ee6789aac7ec21f567a/267c5/URL%20shortener.png","srcSet":"/static/2e0c5b239e172ee6789aac7ec21f567a/267c5/URL%20shortener.png 1x"}}},"cover":{"id":"d4f05d44-e9f3-57e7-bcbb-2c6457ed3211","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/URL shortener.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"6eeb0357-4577-5323-b8f3-12367bbdcba6","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":1000,"height":420,"src":"/static/2e0c5b239e172ee6789aac7ec21f567a/a8734/URL%20shortener.png","srcSet":"/static/2e0c5b239e172ee6789aac7ec21f567a/a8734/URL%20shortener.png 1x"},